				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<div><br><blockquote><hr>Merloc-DEV wrote:<br><div>Hello Everyone,</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Before I get too far along, I thought I'd ask for some feedback from players on how they view different stats with respect to the class(es) they play.&nbsp; Obviously, I have my own view on things, but I'd like to know how any why people have their own views.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>What I'd like, is for you to&nbsp;take a look at this list of the basic item stats (feel free to include any others that I left out), and let me know how and why they think they are, or aren't, important to your class.&nbsp; All comments are useful, and feel free to use current items as examples to illustrate your points if you feel the need.&nbsp; Be sure to INCLUDE THE CLASS name, so I can put your feedback in context.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Hopefully, I'll gain some new insights that will help me do my job better.</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Thanks.</div>
<div><br><hr><br>Since you have been playing a wizard you already know this, but just to be on the same page:<br>&nbsp;</div>
<div>-------<br>CLASS: Wizard<br></div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HP: Semi-important. We don't tank, but we take AE.<br>Mana: Top importance. An OOM wizard is a waste of space and heals. The situation today is better than it was 1.5 yr ago thanks to 2 mana efficient nukes, but still - once your mana is gone you become useless.<br>Endurance: Zero use.<br>AC: Don't care. We don't tank. When taking an occasional hit from a kited mob avoidance is a lot more importnat.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HP Regen: Not important. Especially with HoT potions.<br>Mana Regen: THE Top Importance. Sustained DPS is our weakest spot.<br>Endurance Regen: Zero use.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Strength: Zero use.<br>Stamina: Zero use. (a few extra HP don't make a difference)<br>Agility: Low importance. Helps avoid melee hits, but that not something a wizard does all the time.<br>Dexterity: Zero use.<br>Charisma: Zero use.<br>Intelligence: Important only at low-medium levels. Very easily maxed with today's gear at top levels.<br>Wisdom: Zero use.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Cold Resist: Very important (extremely important for raiders). Resisting (at least partially) big AEs means the difference between life and death.<br>Disease Resist: same<br>Poison Resist: same<br>Magic Resist: same<br>Fire Resist: same </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Attack: Zero use.<br>Delay: Zero use.<br>Damage: Zero use.<br>Range: Semi-important. Good for kiting.<br> </div>
<div>Haste: Spell haste -- Very important.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Combat Effects: Almost zero use (meleeing with a proc weapon is more of an entertainment than practical for a wizard).<br>Shielding: Low importance. We don't tank on a continous basis.<br>Stun Resist: Very important. Both for solo play (not getting stunned by occasional hits) and for raids with nasty stun AE.<br>Strikethrough: Zero use.<br>Spell Shield: Very important for raiders.<br>Avoidance: Semi-important for solo/group players. Less so for raiders.<br>Accuracy: Zero use.<br>DOT Shielding: Very important for raiders. Less so for soloing against DoT casting mobs (HoT potions easily cover normal mob DoTs).<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Skill Mods: Very important for Evocation.<br>Click Effects: Important, depending on the clicky. Epic 2.0 is good. Clicky nukes are good.<br>Proc Effects: Almost zero use (see Combat Effects).<br>Worn Effects: Worn mana regen -- Extremely important.<br>Focus Effects: Very important. And need to get back on par with melee foci/mods. The randomness of 1..N% yields diminishing results.<br>-------</div><br></blockquote></div>
				
				</td></tr>
