				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<DIV>
<DIV>-------<BR>CLASS: Ranger in a DK raiding guild</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP:&nbsp; Very important, HP is the stat that never stops giving<BR>Mana: Important <BR>Endurance: Not important since we have no way to use it anyway<BR>AC: Important </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP Regen: Important although at the levels of gear I have the cap is easy enough to reach<BR>Mana Regen: Important&nbsp;FT seems a tad rare on ranger items especially in the sub Demiplane levels <BR>Endurance Regen:&nbsp; not important see earlier comment</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Strength: Str seems hard to come by on ranger gear though it like other stats aren't really that important<BR>Stamina: Sta on ranger gear at the high end is pretty decent no real complaints there<BR>Agility:&nbsp; Agi is a tad rare on midlevel ranger gear but overall isn't too bad<BR>Dexterity:&nbsp; Dex is overflowing on ranger gear<BR>Charisma:&nbsp;Useful if you do alot of Traq pulling or get DI cast on you seems a bit hard to cap with ranger gear but not to aweful<BR>Intelligence: who cares&nbsp;<BR>Wisdom: Ranger gear seems to be overflowing with wisdom so everything seems good in this regard</DIV>
<DIV>On stats in general other than stamina they seem for the most part to have too big of an actual visable affect in the game so they would seldom be weighed over other more important factors in gear selection</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cold Resist: important though is reasonably represented in ranger gear<BR>Disease Resist: important&nbsp; reasonably represented in ranger gear<BR>Poison Resist:&nbsp; important&nbsp; reasonably represented in ranger gear<BR>Magic Resist: Important doesn't seem to be reasonably represented in ranger gear<BR>Fire Resist:&nbsp; important&nbsp; reasonably represented in ranger gear</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Attack: Imporant upto 300 after that irrelevant. ATK was pretty common on time level gear but was rather difficult to aquire on GOD to CoA gear problem seemed resolved post CoA<BR>Delay: this is pretty much tied to damage in the ratio in the end the delay is less important than the ratio of the weapon in quesstion as is the actual damage, though said delay must be considered when determining actual ratio rather than simple ratio do to the application of the damage bonus on mainhand. Additionaly extremely low delay weaponry have a problem with increasing the vulnerability to Damage shields at the same time they maximize the effectiveness of +damage augs<BR>Damage: see above</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Note on damage/delay for bows in general bows in CoA and above just isn't cutting it. Currently each of these 3 bows are extremely underpowered compared to their melee equivelents based on the 85% criteria that has been stated in the past by the developers as a target for bow dps. Ladwenae can get you actual parses and concrete data but essentially in order to hit the 85% of melee target each of these bows need about 25 added to their base damage</DIV>
<DIV><BR>Range: 200+ please <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>Haste: Important: for any melee centric class haste is extremely important.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Combat Effects: Relatively important more procs =more dps though not as important as other stats<BR>Shielding: This is important for the raiding ranger and seems to be quite lacking in our high end gear<BR>Stun Resist : Important also very much lacking on much high end ranger gear<BR>Strikethrough: somewhat important seems to be relatively well represented on the gear available to us<BR>Spell Shield: see sheilding<BR>Avoidance: Important but seems to be relatively well represented on high end raid gear<BR>Accuracy: this is one that I focus on quite a bit it is very important but also relatively easy to cap at the high end.<BR>DOT Shielding: once again important to the raiding ranger though it does seem to be more common on our gear than the other types of shielding</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Skill Mods: Mis them would like to see some return<BR>Click Effects: Not enough of them, Would really like to see a few more overhaste items available at the high end prefereably items other than range slots (Ranger class item mayhaps? ;-) Proc Effects: Proc's are fun and many are useful for extra DPS important though behind ratio<BR>Worn Effects: Imporant<BR>Focus Effects: Imporant</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A note on effects and mods for hybrids we end up in a rough position since we are both casters and melee and in order to attain maximum effectiveness we need both casting and Melee foci. As such items with no foci particularly visable armor slots (see the last two high end ranger wearable sleeves) are particularly annoying please try to avoid this sort of thing in the future.<BR>-------</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>One will notice going through the list that there are very few things I don't value as a ranger. This will probably hold relatively common with all the hybrids to a far greater degree than either of the pure classes. This is pretty much do to the fact that we have both a casting and a melee focus. Rangers are a very versatile class with no single overwelming strength relying instead on a wide and varied toolset&nbsp; to get the job done. As such we cannot get away with focusing on just one aspect of our class to the exclusion of all others. As a ranger not only do I have to worry about offensive melee stats and effects&nbsp;but also defensive as well as all but a couple of&nbsp;focus effects&nbsp;(poison and desease are pretty much the only types of spells we don't have)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As such well thought out itemization is extremely important to the&nbsp;effectiveness of the class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Oh and while your at it can you at least bump the AC on our class DP item to be on par with the Zerker item?</DIV></DIV>
				
