age per spell cast on us - Quite Important<br>Avoidance:&nbsp; Not getting hit is better than getting hit for less - Very Important.<br>Accuracy: Makes us hit more with our hammers - Not important.<br>DOT Shielding: Less damage per DoT cast on us - Quite Important<br></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Skill Mods: Kinda important - Would love to see some more Alteration skill mods, but they have minimal effect currently and are just for show.<br>Click Effects: Very Important - Always fun to have, plus the +mana regen and +manapool clickies are very important to clerics.<br>Proc Effects: Kinda Important -&nbsp; We have our hammers, nuff said.<br>Worn Effects: Not really Important - Improved Dodge is one of the more important ones we can actually use and the returns for clerics are small.<br>Focus Effects: Very Important - Extended Range, Improved Healing and Mana Preservation are vital. Not seeing as many Mana Preservation focii out there as you used to a few years back (Read: All Caster/Priest Elemental armor sets had Mana Preservation on them somewhere, which has sadly not continued in future quest armor lines), but the other two are easily attainable for us.<br>-------</div><div></div>
				
