				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<div></div><div>-------<br>CLASS:&nbsp; Monk<br></div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HP: Important.&nbsp; This is obvious.&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br>Mana: don't care.<br>Endurance: Semi-important, but pool size only postpones the inevitable point where we're stuck regenerating it at a ridiculously low rate.<br>AC: Semi imporant, up to a point.&nbsp; I'm not sure where AC caps for monks are, but it's not something that I actively search for in my upgrades.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HP Regen:&nbsp; I'm almost capped, albeit unintentionally.&nbsp; not super important. <br>Mana Regen: don't care.<br>Endurance Regen: would love to see this implemented, but in a responsible way so as not to overpower certain classes(zerkers, mostly)<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;<br>[these aren't super important to me, as they all max in post-time raiding.&nbsp; for the casual monks, more agility and more dex]<br></div>
<div>Strength: capped <br>Stamina: capped<br>Agility: capped(took me longest to cap)<br>Dexterity: capped<br>Charisma: don't care<br>Intelligence: don't care<br>Wisdom: it's pretty high, as I share an armor archetype with druids/beasts.&nbsp; i don't tradeskill, so it's not super important to me.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Cold Resist: <br>Disease Resist: <br>Poison Resist: One of my weakest points<br>Magic Resist: High end monk gear is sorely lacking in MR, the rest are pretty easy to pile on.<br>Fire Resist: </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Attack: Important.&nbsp; I'd rather overdo it than underdo it, as atk is important to our dps.<br>Delay: Important.&nbsp; Recent parses are showing favorable dps situations to lower delay weapons even in offhand weapons, as our dual wield rate gets higher and higher.<br>Damage: Obviously important.&nbsp; <br>Range: Monk ranged dps is a joke.&nbsp; I know this isn't the responsibility of the itemization dev, but some kind of range disc for monks would be nice, but nothing overpowered so as not to step on the toes of our neighborhood rogues.<br> </div>
<div>Haste: Would like to see more 45% items, or higher.&nbsp; I have clickable 50% haste, and I'd like to be able to cap or be close to cap when I solo.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Combat Effects:&nbsp; Procs play a pretty important role in our dps, and this mod is probably the hardest for us to cap.<br>Shielding: Semi-important for offtanking situations, or ae. <br>Stun Resist: Important for pulling.&nbsp; Getting stunned on high end raids can lead to death if we aren't quick on the feign death button.<br>Strikethrough: Fairly important, but also common on monk gear.<br>Spell Shield: I value this stat a lot at the level of raiding that I'm on(Tacvi, about to break anguish).&nbsp; It helps tremendously with AE's.<br>Avoidance: Very important, and fairly easy to cap.&nbsp; I'm not one to turn down avoidance gear.&nbsp; <br>Accuracy:&nbsp; Extremely important from a dps standpoint.&nbsp; I dps more than I pull on raids nowadays, and would like to see more accuracy on gear.&nbsp; I go out of my way to get gear with accuracy on it.<br>DOT Shielding:&nbsp; I don't value this as highly as I value spell shield, but it's nice to have.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Skill Mods: I love the block mod on my time tunic, and the dodge mod on my neck piece(GoD tongue samples quest) and wouldn't mind seeing this on gear more often.<br>Click Effects: Clickies are fun.&nbsp; I'd like to see more overhaste options(especially at the lower end, even some 3% clickies for easier raids would be nice just to have options.&nbsp; As it stands, there are only a few:&nbsp; Quarm Ear, Tacvi Ring, Zoo Event in Qvic ear, RSS Royals cape, OMM Range, and Mayong Range.&nbsp; I've never seen the ear drop from the zoo event.<br>Proc Effects: See my above statements regarding combat effects.&nbsp; Procs are nice.&nbsp; I'd also like to see more non-elemental +damage augs.&nbsp; The last two expansions have been good about that for monks(Eye of Lycanthrope, and the deathknell 3 dmg+lifetap aug). <br>Worn Effects: All are important.<br>Focus Effects: I'd like to see endurance conservation focuses.<br>-------<br><br>Here's my magelo for a point of reference, if that helps:<br><br>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1077519<br><br>edit:&nbsp; I wholeheartely agree with the above poster's message about wanting to look like a monk.&nbsp; I don't want leather tunics.&nbsp; I dont' want to look like a druid or a human beastlord.&nbsp; I'd like more chestwrap options, or NPC's that you can turn your armor into for chestwrap options.&nbsp; I don't like shoulderpads;&nbsp; i'd prefer armbands.&nbsp; I like fistwraps, and small unobtrusive bracers.&nbsp; <br><br>The robe look from robe of the lost circle with old models, where the monk still appears bare chested but has the long draping robes-- this is very cool and I'd love to see it with luclin models.&nbsp; Helmets are ugly.&nbsp; I'd love to see actual headbands implemented.<br><br>Weight is a concern as well.&nbsp; I'd like more coin weight reduction options, as it's a crappy deal when I'm farming for plat and I either have to destroy money, or run and bank because I'm losing armor class due to heavy coinage.<br></div><div></div><p>Message Edited by Wonton_Noodle on <span class=date_text>07-06-2006</span> <span class=time_text>06:33 PM</span>
				
				</td></tr>
